  "name": "RPlog_When_Corellians_Meet",
  "title": "Two Corellians at the Cat's Claw",
  "summary": "At the Cat's Claw bar on Ord Mantell, New Republic FleetOps officer Argon Brand, commander of the Corellian gunship Lightbringer, strikes up a conversation with the sullen fighter pilot Chanara Thorn, drawn together by their shared Corellian roots and love of whiskey and starships. They trade banter about Corellian shipbuilding, Argon's war record at Bothawui, and the politics of the New Republic versus the Empire. Chana reveals she works for the independent Johanna te Danaan, that she took an oath to the long-dead Old Republic, and that she spent forty-three years frozen in carbonite, waking only four years ago. Argon offers to look into veteran benefits and help if she ever needs it, though Chana privately hopes no records of her survive. The two part on warm terms, exchanging comlink codes and the customary blessing, May the Force be with you.",
